Vice President Mike Pence spoke with Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko to express the United States' ongoing support for Ukraine's fight against Russian aggression, efforts to improve governance, and economic reforms. They also discussed the importance of expanding trade and investment between the two countries. Pence emphasized the need for continued reforms in fighting corruption, increasing transparency, and improving the business climate. He reiterated that the U.S. will hold Russia accountable until it fulfills its commitments under the Minsk agreements, returns Crimea to Ukraine, and stops its destabilizing activities.